Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: PermeaDerm develops products to help protect, support, and aid in healing weakened or damaged tissue. it is committed to understanding the unmet needs of acute and chronic wounds as well as hernia and soft tissue repair. PermeaDerm focuses on the art of passage of fluid adjacent to the wound beneath the primary dressing into a secondary absorbent dressing as well as the kinetics of uninterrupted wound healing. The technology of this research will evolve into a product called PermeaDerm dressing which possesses all the characteristics and attributes known to be important for optimal wound healing, as well as new advances that result in minimization of wound desiccation and infection complication. The technology and design for soft tissue and hernia repair are intended to minimize adhesions and chronic pain and provide a 3D compliant structure that facilitates autogenous tissue ingrowth which is believed to minimize latent infections. Aubrey Woodroof founded PermeaDerm in Carlsbad, California in 2013.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering
